ts, and delaying marriage, ultimately failing to meet what they consider the traditional benchmarks of adulthood. Hashemi follows their stories, one by one, as they try to climb up the proverbial ladder of success.Coming of Age in Iran sheds light on the inner lives of a new generation of Iranian youth as they struggle in the face of ongoing economic crisis.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2021) 0aPoor youthzIran. 0aPovertyzIran. 0aYouthzIranxEconomic conditions. 0aYouthzIranxSocial conditions. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aAccentuated Conformism.  aAgency.  aAppearances.  aAspirations.  aBodily Capital.  aCultural Mimicry.  aCultural Production.  aCulture.  aDignity.  aDrug Use.  aEmbourgeoisement.  aFace Game.  aFace Rules.  aFace.  aFamily Support.  aFeminization of Work.  aHard Work.  aHegemony.  aHorizontal Exchange Networks.  aIncremental Mobility.  aInequality.  aInformal Work.  aKelās.  aMasculinity.  aMoral Capital.  aMoral Pollution.  aMoral Purity.  aMoral Self.  aMorality.  aPre-Existing Resources.  aResistance.  aRisk-Taking.  aRitual Action.  aSari.  aSatellite Television.  aSelf Sufficiency.  aSexual Cleanliness.  aSocial Capital.  aSocial Media.  aSocial Mobility.  aSocial Ties.  aSocioeconomic Mobility.  aStatus.  aStreet Smarts.  aSymbolic Boundaries.  aTastemaking.  aTehran.  aThe Gaze.  aVertical Exchange Networks.  aYouth.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package